"""B1/B2 — seed constellation + TPS expansion.

B1: enumerate candidate 4–6-point CZ constellations ranked by (a) convex-hull
  emptiness (i.e., near pia surface), (b) tight intra-cluster spacing, and
  (c) feature-cosine coherence.  Build an anisotropy-invariant descriptor per
  cluster (sorted pairwise-distance histogram ratio) and search matching
  descriptors in HCR.  Intrinsic confidence = descriptor-distance margin plus
  seed-residual ratio after one-step anisotropic fit + TPS on held-out nearby
  cells.

B2: grow the landmark set from B1 seed by per-axis TPS + k-NN neighbour
  matching.  Intrinsic gate on TPS residual (vs 3σ of nearby actives) plus
  1-NN topology agreement.
"""
from __future__ import annotations

